OL,3,CActivists who block roads could be
OL,4,Cforced to pay compensation, report
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,F"Number 10 really sees the politics of
OL,8,Fbeing able to give more power to
OL,9,Findividuals to be able to do this.
OL,10,FEvery time it happens, you have
OL,11,Fintense frustration for individuals
OL,12,Fwho take things into their own hands
OL,13,Fbut are ultimately powerless when they
OL,14,Fcannot get to where they are going.
OL,16,F"People organising these blockades are
OL,17,Fnot seeing sufficient deterrent from
OL,18,Findividual prosecutions. It is about
OL,19,Fhow much it will be worthwhile for
OL,20,Fthem to do it if these proposals are
OL,21,Fenacted."
