OL,3,CActivists who block roads could be
OL,4,Cforced to pay compensation, report
OL,5,Csuggests
OL,7,FThe newspaper suggested the
OL,8,Fcompensation scheme could be modelled
OL,9,Fon the small claims court system or
OL,10,Falong the lines of the financial
OL,11,Fservices ombudsman.
OL,13,FThe review by Lord Walney, the
OL,14,Fcrossbench peer who as John Woodcock
OL,15,Fwas a former Labour MP, is intended to
OL,16,Fincrease the Government's
OL,17,Funderstanding of the increase in
OL,18,Factivity by far-right, far-left and
OL,19,Fother political groups and identify
OL,20,Fwhere activities can cross into
OL,21,Fcriminality and disruption.
